  <static seed="100" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionApplication/FractionSubtractionWordProblems30.pg">
    <statement><p>Each page of a book is <m>{4{\textstyle\frac{1}{2}}}</m> inches in height, and consists of a header (a top margin), a footer (a bottom margin), and the middle part (the body). The header is <m>{{\frac{5}{7}}}</m> of an inch thick and the middle part is <m>{3{\textstyle\frac{5}{7}}}</m> inches from top to bottom.</p>
<p>What is the thickness of the footer?</p>
<p>The footer is <fillin characters="11" name="AnSwEr0001"/> of an inch thick.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>{\frac{1}{14}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>From a page<rsq/>s total height, we subtract the thickness of the header and the height of the body to find the thickness of the footer:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ 
\begin{aligned}[t]
   {4{\textstyle\frac{1}{2}}} - {{\frac{5}{7}}} - {3{\textstyle\frac{5}{7}}}
      \amp = 4 + \frac{1}{2} -{{\frac{5}{7}}} - 3 - {{\frac{5}{7}}} \\
      \amp = 1 + \frac{1}{2} -{{\frac{5}{7}}} - {{\frac{5}{7}}} \\
      \amp = \frac{1}{1} + \frac{1}{2} -{{\frac{5}{7}}} - {{\frac{5}{7}}} \\
      \amp = \frac{1 \cdot 14}{1 \cdot 14} + \frac{1\cdot7}{2\cdot7} - \frac{5\cdot2}{7\cdot2} - \frac{5\cdot2}{7\cdot2} \\
      \amp =  \frac{14}{14} + \frac{7}{14} - \frac{10}{14} - \frac{10}{14} \\
      \amp = \frac{14+7-10-10}{14} \\
      \amp = {{\frac{1}{14}}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>The footer is <m>{{\frac{1}{14}}}</m> inches thick.</p>
</solution>
